            "author_info": {
                "name": "Lola Sugimoto",
                "href": "/profile/\u6749\u672c-\u30ed\u30fc\u30e9-Lola-Sugimoto"
            },
            "answer_text": "I think many of the skirts do have pockets, but according to high school girls who have answered this very question (in Japanese) on the internet, they use their blazer pockets in winter or their blouse pockets in hotter weather more often. Why not use the skirt pocket? A lot of girls fold the waist of their skirt to shorten the length, and the pockets get folded too. But these girls carry enormous, extremely heavy bags that contain tons of books and miscellaneous other real or perceived necessities. Think a bag about the size of what would normally contain gym clothes and sports equipment for an athletically inclined adult. Tissues? Probably. A giant mirror? Sure. I even knew a girl who always had sweet potatoes. They love hanging little stuffed animals or other charms off their bags, too, like this, but often to greater excess:  It\u2019s a way to express style and individuality. ",
