            "answer_text": "As a rule, no, there aren't any pockets. But virtually all HS students, boys and girls alike, have book bags- backpacks, satchels, and so on. Many students have bags within their bags for women\u2019s products, a thermos or bottle, a cloth or tissue for a quick dab at sweat, and so on. Most HS bags have more than a single compartment to accommodate this: a large compartment for textbooks, a smaller compartment for notebooks, and even smaller compartments for boxed lunches, train passes, pencils and erasers, etc. ",
